abstract: Trump administration officials have rescheduled for March 11 a critical meeting to discuss potential new U.S. restrictions on sales of technology to Huawei and China, people familiar with the matter said.
snippet: Trump administration officials have rescheduled for March 11 a critical meeting to discuss potential new U.S. restrictions on sales of technology to Huawei and China, people familiar with the matter said.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK/WASHINGTON — Trump administration officials have rescheduled for March 11 a critical meeting to discuss potential new U.S. restrictions on sales of technology to Huawei and China, people familiar with the matter said.
headline_main: U.S. Moves High-Level U.S. Meeting on China Tech, Possible New Huawei Curbs to March: Sources
headline_print_headline: U.S. Moves High-Level U.S. Meeting on China Tech, Possible New Huawei Curbs to March: Sources

abstract: The Trump administration on Friday said it would focus on concluding new trade agreements with Britain, the European Union and Kenya over the coming year, while strictly enforcing trade laws and pushing for reforms of the World Trade Organization.
snippet: The Trump administration on Friday said it would focus on concluding new trade agreements with Britain, the European Union and Kenya over the coming year, while strictly enforcing trade laws and pushing for reforms of the World Trade Organization.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Friday said it would focus on concluding new trade agreements with Britain, the European Union and Kenya over the coming year, while strictly enforcing trade laws and pushing for reforms of the World Trade Organization.
headline_main: USTR Vows to Push for Trade Deals With Britain, EU; Seeks Reforms at WTO
headline_print_headline: USTR Vows to Push for Trade Deals With Britain, EU; Seeks Reforms at WTO

abstract: A top aide to President Donald Trump complained Friday that the news media doesn't pay enough attention to the president's loving relationship with his 13-year-old son, Barron.
snippet: A top aide to President Donald Trump complained Friday that the news media doesn't pay enough attention to the president's loving relationship with his 13-year-old son, Barron.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A top aide to President Donald Trump complained Friday that the news media doesn't pay enough attention to the president's loving relationship with his 13-year-old son, Barron.
headline_main: Aide: Media Ignores Trump's Loving Bond With 13-Year-Old Son
headline_print_headline: Aide: Media Ignores Trump's Loving Bond With 13-Year-Old Son

abstract: A federal judge shot down a challenge to the copyright of the Woody Guthrie folk anthem, blocking an attempt to put it in the public domain.
snippet: A federal judge shot down a challenge to the copyright of the Woody Guthrie folk anthem, blocking an attempt to put it in the public domain.
lead_paragraph: First, “Happy Birthday to You” lost its copyright. Then “We Shall Overcome” became public domain as well.

abstract: Rush Limbaugh and Fox News pundits accused Democrats and journalists of “politicizing and actually weaponizing” an infectious disease.
snippet: Rush Limbaugh and Fox News pundits accused Democrats and journalists of “politicizing and actually weaponizing” an infectious disease.
lead_paragraph: The stock market is swooning. Consumers are stockpiling masks and antibacterial gels. President Trump’s response to a global epidemic has done little to quell fears.

abstract: A divided U.S. appeals court handed President Donald Trump a major legal victory on Friday by dismissing a Democratic-led congressional panel's lawsuit seeking to enforce a subpoena for testimony from former White House Counsel Donald McGahn.
snippet: A divided U.S. appeals court handed President Donald Trump a major legal victory on Friday by dismissing a Democratic-led congressional panel's lawsuit seeking to enforce a subpoena for testimony from former White House Counsel Donald McGahn.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A divided U.S. appeals court handed President Donald Trump a major legal victory on Friday by dismissing a Democratic-led congressional panel's lawsuit seeking to enforce a subpoena for testimony from former White House Counsel Donald McGahn.
headline_main: Trump Wins Bid to Block McGahn Testimony Sought by House Democrats
headline_print_headline: Trump Wins Bid to Block McGahn Testimony Sought by House Democrats

abstract: It is not clear if the Republican congressman from Texas, whose name was floated for the post last year, can win Senate confirmation.
snippet: It is not clear if the Republican congressman from Texas, whose name was floated for the post last year, can win Senate confirmation.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump announced on Friday that he intended to nominate Representative John Ratcliffe, Republican of Texas, as his director of national intelligence, choosing someone he considered last summer before senior Republicans in Congress deemed him unqualified for the job.

abstract: President Donald Trump on Friday picked Rep. John Ratcliffe again to be the nation's top intelligence official, just months after abruptly ending an earlier effort to install him amid bipartisan criticism that the Texas Republican was unqualified for the post.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Friday picked Rep. John Ratcliffe again to be the nation's top intelligence official, just months after abruptly ending an earlier effort to install him amid bipartisan criticism that the Texas Republican was unqualified ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump on Friday picked Rep. John Ratcliffe again to be the nation's top intelligence official, just months after abruptly ending an earlier effort to install him amid bipartisan criticism that the Texas Republican was unqualified for the post.
headline_main: Trump Picks Ratcliffe as Top Intelligence Official, Again
headline_print_headline: Trump Picks Ratcliffe as Top Intelligence Official, Again

abstract: An appeals court dismissed a lawsuit brought by the House Judiciary Committee against President Trump’s former White House counsel, Donald F. McGahn II.
snippet: An appeals court dismissed a lawsuit brought by the House Judiciary Committee against President Trump’s former White House counsel, Donald F. McGahn II.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal appeals court ruled on Friday that Congress could not sue to enforce its subpoenas of executive branch officials, handing a major victory to President Trump and dealing a severe blow to the power of Congress to conduct oversight.
